# Graphify-first navigation

Before broad `Grep` / `Glob` / exploring many files for architecture or “where is X?”, start with the code graph:

1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` — Summary + **Community Hubs** — pick the 1–3 communities that match the task.
2. Open that community section in the same report (or related paths listed there) and only then read those source files.
3. For relationship questions (who calls / imports whom), prefer `graphify-out/graph.json` or the HTML graph over scanning the whole tree.
4. After substantial code edits in a session, run `graphify update .` (AST-only, no LLM cost) so the graph stays current.
5. If `GRAPH_REPORT.md` “Built from commit” ≠ `git rev-parse --short HEAD`, refresh with `graphify update .` before trusting it.

## Do not

- Dump all of `GRAPH_REPORT.md` or `graph.json` into context — read targeted sections only.
- Skip graphify for tiny, known-path edits (e.g. user already gave the exact file).
- Use graphify instead of reading the actual file when implementing — graph points you there; source remains truth.

## Handy communities (this repo)

- PDP / product page → Product Detail Pages, Product Hero Section, Product Detail Data Provider
- Homepage reviews/stories → Testimonials and Reviews, Patient Reviews UI
- Checkout / header → Checkout and Site Header, Checkout UI Components
- Quiz → Dynamic Quiz Logic, Quiz Data Constants
